# Rust
/target
**/target/
**/*.rs.bk

# Java / barback
*.class
**/dependency-reduced-pom.xml

# CycloneDX SBOMs (generated by scripts/generate-sbom.sh / cargo-cyclonedx /
# the cyclonedx-maven-plugin). These are build artifacts published to the
# release, never committed to the tree. cargo-cyclonedx writes a
# `<crate>.cdx.json` next to every workspace Cargo.toml; the merged/staged
# product SBOMs land under `dist/` (also ignored via the leading `/target`
# /scratch-dir conventions, but listed explicitly here for clarity).
*.cdx.json
/dist/

# Editors / OS
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# Local environment
.env
*.env.local

# Generated docs
/docs/api/

# corpus checkouts are materialized on-demand and not tracked
test-corpus/*/checkout/

# Network-traffic captures from `barista-netcap` benchmark sessions.
# HAR files can be large and contain timing information specific to one
# host; the canonical store is Cloudflare R2 (see
# `bench/captures/README.md`). The local tree is a scratch space.
#
# We exclude everything under `bench/captures/` *except* the README and
# the `.gitkeep` sentinel, which document the layout for new operators.
# The `!`-negation pattern only works when the parent directory itself
# isn't excluded, so we list children rather than gitignoring the dir.
bench/captures/*/
bench/captures/*.har
bench/captures/*.log
bench/captures/*.toml
